description: Returns a list of all Outposts buckets in an Outpost that are owned by the authenticated sender of the request. For more information, see Using Amazon S3 on Outposts in the Amazon S3 User Guide. For an example of the request syntax for Amazon S3 on Outposts that uses the S3 on Outposts endpoint hostname prefix and x-amz-outpost-id in your request, see the Examples section.

parameters.name: AccountId
parameters.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID of the Outposts bucket.

parameters.name: OutpostId
parameters.description: The ID of the Outposts resource.

nested_items.name: BucketArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the regional bucket.

nested_items.name: CreationDate
nested_items.description: The creation date of the regional bucket.

nested_items.name: OutpostId
nested_items.description: The Outposts ID of the regional bucket.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: NextToken is sent when isTruncated is true, which means there are more buckets that can be listed. The next list requests to Amazon S3 can be continued with this NextToken. NextToken is obfuscated and is not a real key.
